    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "         At 10:45 a.m., July 7, 1947, I talked to SAC Johnson of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Milwaukee Office concerning the United Press item appearing in the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "Washington Post for Monday, July 7, with reference to a flying disc",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "or flying saucer allegedly reported to the Milwaukee Office by",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "Reverend Joseph Brasky of St. Joseph's Church, Grafton, Wisconsin.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "         SAC Johnson advised that the Associated Press and the United",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "Press between the hours 1:00 and 6:00 a.m. today had made inquiry of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "him as to whether anything had been reported to the Milwaukee Office.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "He declined to comment.  He stated as a matter of fact the priest had",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "not made any contact with him, and he learned from the Associated Press",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "that the priest was intoxicated and as far as the Associated Press was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "concerned they were not releasing the story because all that was involved",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "was a circular saw.  Mr. Johnson stated the Milwaukee Sentinel apparently",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "sent the report out and that they handled United Press service.  He stated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "a photograph of the priest was in this morning's paper holding a circular",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "saw which apparently covers the body of the priest from arm pit to arm pit.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "Attached to the saw are several wires and two small tubes described as",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "about three inches long and one inch in diameter.  The news item in the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "Milwaukee Sentinel indicates it was believed some prankster had thrown it",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "into the yard, perhaps with a firecracker attached.  Mr. Johnson stated the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "Milwaukee Sentinel had stated the priest would make a report of this matter",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "today to the Milwaukee Office.  I instructed SAC Johnson in the event the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "priest made a report to furnish details of the report immediately, but in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "view of the nature of the information in his possession, no inquiry should",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "be conducted at the present.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
